texts.text: *Pant*
It's over, Marici.
But you did well all things considered.
At this point, you'll have a tough time even against my minions.
*Wince*
It's no use, just yield.
I'll make sure you don't suffer so...
Devil Download!
That was close. Did we make it in time?
...You again?
Yeah. We're not stopping until we stop you.
You're very lucky, Marici.
But I wonder how much longer you actually have...
>Tzitzimitl turns her back on everyone.
Exposing you back like that seems careless, don't you think?
Go!
*Roar*
Ha!
*Scream*
One-shot...? She's gotten stronger.
Didn't I say that I have no desire to face you?
You keep sayin' that, but we ain't givin' up.
We need to stop you.
And why are you trying to destroy the world?
Do you hate our world that much?
Questioning my motivations and asking why...
This is why there is no point in facing you.
...Anyways.
By destroying the world, I'll never see the likes of you again.
But if you wish to know that much.
Fine, I'll tell you.
Huh?
It is my purpose. Simply that.
So, it's your goal. Right?
You're tasked with destroying the world, but it's really your desire to... No?
No. Fools.
How much more do I need to dumb this down.
I am Tzitzimitl.
I will end the cycle of the Fifth Sun and descend upon your world to destroy it.
It's "fate". That is all.
Understand?
Anything beyond that is none of my concern.
What the hell do you mean by that?
I should be asking you that. What more do you need?
My purpose is simply to destroy your world.
You could not understand what it is like to have that go unfulfilled,
since you humans live and die without a care in the world!
Since the cycle of the Fifth Sun began,
for eons, each day and night, I've continued battling against the sun to no avail.
I've continued existing as the one that destroys the world,
but haven't been able to because of that accursed thing...!
>Tzitzimitl points to the sun that's now roughly 70% consumed by darkness.
I've been toiling for hundreds, thousands of years, to destroy it.
By any means necessary, I wanted to destroy the sun!
And then someone... Or "something" granted me that wish and this world was born.
"Something"? What do you mean by that?
Do you know why this space exists?
Who knows? I don't care one way or the other.
It just felt that way is all.
I mean, don't I feel a bit too at home here?
Regardless, it doesn't matter to me what this place is.
The important part is that I can use this place to accomplish my goal.
It doesn't matter who or what made this place.
That imitation... A sun not protected by its precious god.
His pawn is also nothing here.
There's not a thing anyone can do to stop me...
*Wince*
Then we'll take the place of the sun god, yo.
What...?
Yo, we'll stop you and your stupid plans.
Ain't no way we're lettin' you do this.
But...
Passionate as ever.
So lame. And dull. And dumb.
Wha...!
But I won't say no.
Right, we're all ready to go!
I didn't say that.
We're going to stop you.
We're not going to lose.

*Snicker*
*Laugh*
You? Replace the sun god?
Don't make me laugh...! What?!
You let your guard down...!
>An arrow of light pierces Tzitzimitl and goes straight through.

*Wince*
Ugh... You stubborn bitch...!
*Snicker*
You really don't have the strength to actually fight me?
>Tzitzimitl slowly rises to the air.
This is nothing more than a scratch...
But I did let my guard down for letting myself rant for so long.
I've come to my senses. It's high time that I ended this.
...! What, you're running?!
Yes, of course.
When the sun becomes fully consumes, it will be the end of Marici.
Neither she nor you can live such an existence.
On top of that... Your world is going to be destroyed anyway.
Goodbye, forever.
Marici... And the sun god's replacements.
*Chuckle*
>Tzitzimitl vanishes into the darkness.
Shit... She got away again.
*Groan*
Marici... Are you alright?
I... I must ask of you...
My power now is not even a third of what it was....
I'll only grow weaker as the eclipse continues...
And Tzitzimitl only grows stronger...
I no longer have the ability to defeat her.
But...
Don't say that.
But I shall not yield.
Yes. I shall not yield.
...By the sun god's strength, and as his servant.
I am willing to believe in your abilities now.
Us?
Yes... She is bound to return to me.
When that happens... I cannot let it end there.
I will certainly be overwhelmed by the other demons.
Which is why I must ask for your aid.
...Yes, of course.
Let's find Tzitzimitl and stop her once and for all!
